2. mariadb.yaml and quiz-service.yaml — spec.template.metadata.spec invalid field
This is a YAML indentation bug. You have spec nested under metadata inside the pod template instead of at the same level as metadata

3. Vault never starts → everything downstream fails
The kubectl wait uses label app.kubenetes.io/name=vault — note the typo: kubenetes instead of kubernetes. This means the wait finds no pod and times out immediately. Fix in your Makefile (lines 91 and 96):
4. main-service never created
It's not in the error output at all, which means kubectl apply -f srcs/k8s/base/main-service.yaml either errored silently or the file has the same spec.template.metadata.spec bug. Check that file too.
5. Port-forward failing
This is a cascade — once the above are fixed and pods are actually Running, port-forward will work. The kube-forward  also has a structural issue: the & backgrounded commands followed by wait will hang forever. For a make target that's fine if intentional, but if you want it non-blocking just remove the wait.